    "The collaboration has also facilitated student internship experiences and potential job opportunities in the field while opening avenues for additional research funding in cybersecurity.",
    "The work in Andriessen et al. (2022) introduced the COLTRANE Methodology to enhance cybersecurity education by incorporating scenariobased and problem-oriented learning by presenting students with realistic situations.",
    "This approach helps bridge the gap between theory and practice and prepares students for real-world cybersecurity scenarios.",
    "Problem-based learning is essential in the instructional design of the online course on information security (Chandrasekaran and KV, 2023).",
    "Including industry-oriented components in cybersecurity teaching in universities is crucial to bridge the gap between academic knowledge and real-world practices."
